//BASIC SCAN
COMMAND - fierce --domain <target website>

//EXAMPLE - fierce --domain www.google.com. You can also use other options such as:
° --wide - It scans entire class c of discovered records
° --delay - It will wait for the specified time between lookups, etc.


//DESCRIPTION - It is a tool which is used to find hostnames and con-contiguous against specified domains. It uses DNS primarily you will often find mis-configured networks that leak internal address space.

To get more information about the fierce tool type any of the following 2 commands :
*dnsenum -h 
*dnsenum --help
[ Both -h and --help will give the same results :) ]
